  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to Anthy</title>

    <para>
      <application>Anthy</application> is a package for an input method editor backend for Unix-like
      systems for the Japanese language. It can convert Hiragana to Kanji as per the language rules.
      As a preconversion stage, Latin characters (Romaji) can be used to input Hiragana.
      Anthy is commonly used with an input method framework such as
      <application>ibus</application>, <application>fcitx</application> or <application>SCIM</application>.
    </para>

    &lfs75_checked;

